cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of neural networks for optimizing the data processing pipeline in functional Magnetic Resonance Imaging (fMRI) analysis. This involves tasks such as accurate localization of brain activity, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks for optimization also falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the validation of results in a brain decoding experiment, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
